com.bigdata.bop.solutions

Interface IGroupByRewriteState

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    GroupByRewriter

    public interface IGroupByRewriteState
    A rewrite of a GroupByState in which all IAggregate expressions have been lifted out in order to (a) minimize redundancy when computing the aggregates; and (b) simplify the logic required to compute the IAggregates.
    Version:
    $Id$
    Author:
    Bryan Thompson

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      LinkedHashMap<IAggregate<?>,IVariable<?>> getAggExpr()
      The set of all unique IAggregate expressions paired with anonymous variables.
      IConstraint[] getHaving2()

    • Method Detail

      • getAggExpr

        LinkedHashMap<IAggregate<?>,IVariable<?>> getAggExpr()
        The set of all unique IAggregate expressions paired with anonymous variables. Any internal IAggregate have been lifted out and will appear before any IAggregates which use them. The IAggregate MAY have a complex internal IValueExpression, but it WILL NOT have a nested IAggregate.

      • getHaving2

        IConstraint[] getHaving2()
        A modified version of the original HAVING expression which has the same semantics (and null iff the original was null or empty). However, the modified select expressions DO NOT contain any IAggregate functions. All IAggregate functions have been lifted out into #aggExp.

      • getSelect2

        IValueExpression<?>[] getSelect2()
        A modified version of the original SELECT expression which has the same semantics. However, the modified select expressions DO NOT contain any IAggregate functions. All IAggregate functions have been lifted out into #aggExp.
